                    <msContents>
                        <summary> An autograph manuscript produced in 1795 by Ikeda Zuisen on smallpox lesions on the lips and tongue with colour illustrations and preface written by Naguse Tetsu. </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_94">

                            <author key="person_12246716" source="VIAF">
                                <persName xml:lang="ja" source="IANA" type="original">池田瑞仙</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Ikeda Zuisen</persName>
                                <note><p>The author was born in a village in what is now Yamaguchi
                                        Prefecture in the south-west of Japan and learnt what he
                                        knew of medicine there. He developed an interest in smallpox
                                        but since the domain in which he lived had a strict
                                        segregation policy for smallpox sufferers he had few
                                        opportunities to observe the symptoms until he had the
                                        chance to stem an outbreak on the island of Itsukushima. As
                                        a result, his fame spread and in 1797 he entered the service
                                        of the Bakufu in Edo as a specialist in smallpox. He wrote a
                                        number of works on smallpox but none of them were ever
                                        published.</p></note>
                            </author>
                            
                            
                            <author>
                                <persName xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Naguse Tetsu</persName>
                            </author>

                                <title type="original" xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">痘瘡唇舌図</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Tōsō shinzetsuzu</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="en" source="IANA">Illustrations of smallpox on the lips and tongue</title>
                            

                            <explicit><locus/>天明八年歳次戊申秋八月門人紀伊弱［ママ］山斎藤順謹撰／東都長瀬轍書 </explicit>

                            <colophon><locus/>寛政七乙卯年秋九月／錦橋散人池田瑞仙識 </colophon>

                            <filiation>There is one copy extant in Japan and a further one in the library of UCLA. See <ref target="https://kokusho.nijl.ac.jp/?ln=en">Union Catalogue Work ID: 3615552</ref> for copies of 痘瘡唇舌図 held by other institutions.</filiation>

